cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of representing graphs by polygons, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of lower and upper bounds and the development of an algorithm suggest that the paper also belongs to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of planar graphs and their representation is also related to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
